works.description: The start to the 2011 season has been great for Red Bull’s driver Sebastian Vettel. To celebrate his 2010 Formula 1 World Championship, the Formula One star has spent a cool $100,000 on a chopper. Although Vettel hasn’t commented anything related to his new machine, his close friend Kimi Raikkonen has revealed that the F1 driver had commissioned a custom Avalanche chopper from German master motorcycle builder Marcus Walz. The 120bhp motorcycle is 1.78 meters long.
